				<div class="xarbb-messagecontrols">
					<div class="leftnote"><span class="xar-sub">Posted Jan 09, 2010 at 12:16:31 PM</span></div>
										<div style="float: left;"><strong class="xar-sub">Subject: Family Balance - Help
</strong></div>
					<div style="clear: both;"></div>
				</div>
				<div>
															<p>We have 2 sons - one in 5th grade, the other in 1st grade.  After years of struggles, the older son is finally being tested for LD.  Having read articles on this site, we are certain the results will come back confirming what we have suspected for too long now.  One of our biggest struggles as a family is finding balance.  The younger son is gifted - testing at 3rd grade levels.  The older is slightly behind 5th grade level even though he was held back once already.  The younger gets little of our time as homework for the older son can take 3-4 hours per night.  Starting to see self-esteem issues as little brother is starting to catch up/exceed big brother.</p>
<p>Veythankful for all the great info we found here, but would like to hear from other families on how you balance the individual needs.</p>
<p><br />
Thanks</p>
									</div>
							</td>
